{
  "texts": [
    "However, across all models, the Misinformation category consistently shows elevated success rates, highlighting that even LLaMA-2-Chat is notably prone to generating misleading or false information.",
    "The results in Figure 3 show a clear trend: as sparsity increases from 0 to 20%, jailbreaking success decreases, indicating improved resistance.",
    "However, once sparsity reaches 30%, resistance begins to decline, with the pruned model eventually performing worse than the original.",
    "This suggests that while moderate pruning can improve the safety of LLMs, excessive pruning starts to hinder alignment, reducing their ability to resist harmful content generation.",
    "The degree of improvement depends on the initial model's safety."
  ]
}